    "solution": "<p>$$(\\sin 10^\\circ \\,.\\,\\sin 50^\\circ \\,.\\,\\sin 70^\\circ )\\,.\\,(\\sin 10^\\circ \\,.\\,\\sin 20^\\circ \\,.\\,\\sin 40^\\circ )$$</p>\n<p>$$ = \\left( {{1 \\over 4}\\sin 30^\\circ } \\right)\\,.\\,\\left[ {{1 \\over 2}\\sin 10^\\circ (\\cos 20^\\circ  - \\cos 60^\\circ )} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over {16}}\\left[ {\\sin 10^\\circ \\left( {\\cos 20^\\circ  - {1 \\over 2}} \\right)} \\right]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over {32}}[2\\sin 10^\\circ \\,.\\,\\cos 20^\\circ  - \\sin 10^\\circ ]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over {32}}[\\sin 30^\\circ  - \\sin 10^\\circ  - \\sin 10^\\circ ]$$</p>\n<p>$$ = {1 \\over {64}} - {1 \\over {64}}\\sin 10^\\circ $$</p>\n<p>Clearly, $$\\alpha  = {1 \\over {64}}$$</p>\n<p>Hence $$16 + {\\alpha ^{ - 1}} = 80$$</p>",
